which it owned since  in  the company changed its name to lion with national foods becoming a subsequent subsidiary called lion dairy  drinks based in melbourne the company employs over  people the company was formed in  with the merger of ld nathan  co and lion breweries and was listed on both the australian and new zealand stock exchanges under the symbol lnn on  september  lion nathan shareholders overwhelmingly voted to accept a  takeover offer by kirin the takeover was implemented on  october  and the company was delisted contents  history  breweries  castlemaine perkins brewery  south australian brewing company  australian beer brands  j boag  son  castlemaine xxxx  emu brewery  hahn  james squire  regular brews  ciders  speciality brews  little creatures  white rabbit  cider  southwark  swan brewery  tooheys  west end  other brands  new zealand beer brands  speight’s  lion  steinlager  mac’s craft beers mccashins brewery  canterbury draught  emersons brewery  other brands  international brands  brewed under licence  imported under licence  wines  spirits  milk products  capitol chilled foods  nonalcoholic beverages and water ices  see also  references  external links historyedit the original forerunner of the company was brown campbell  co the company of logan campbell and william brown who established the hobson bridge brewery in auckland in  by  it was the largest brewery in the north island if not the country in may  brown campbell  co amalgamated with louis ehrenfrieds albert brewery which he had bought in  to form campbell and ehrenfried the new company was managed by arthur myers ehrenfrieds nephew in  campbell and ehrenfried merged with the great northern brewery which owned the lion brand in  ten breweries amalgamated to form new zealand breweries campbell and ehrenfried merged its breweries into new zealand breweries but remained a separate company douglas myers grandson of arthur myers became ceo of campbell and ehrenfried in  the northern division of new zealand breweries adopted the name lion breweries in  campbell and ehrenfried bought  per cent of lion breweries in  by the late s new zealand breweries had developed into one of new zealands largest companies in  lion breweries took over ld nathan  co new zealands largest retailer which at the time owned woolworths nz to form lion nathan the same year woolworths general merchandise division was rebranded deka with ownership transferred to the farmers trading company in  in  it became an australasian business when it established a major presence in australia by securing management control of bond corporation’s brewing assets including the tooheys brewery in sydney and castlemaine perkins in brisbane in  douglas myers sold most of his  percent share in lion nathan to kirin brewery company of japan in  lion nathan made a takeover bid for the independent south australian coopers brewery the takeover was strongly opposed by coopers management and was rejected at an extraordinary general meeting when  of the shareholders voted in favour of permanently removing the rd tier purchasing rights of lion nathan effectively preventing any current or future takeover bid by  the company was  owned by kirin with the difference made up by australian and new zealand share funds in september  shareholders voted in favour of a complete takeover by kirin holdings in june  the company launched the tap king draught beer product that is sold with a co gas chamber so that consumers can drink draught beer at home lionel richie appeared in a television commercial to promote the device and reportedly received a million to appear in the promotional campaign the introduction of the tap king caused controversy due to the perceived impact upon alcohol venues concerns were raised in regard to lower patronage rates for venues due to a greater incentive for consumers to drink beer in home environments breweriesedit the company owns a number of breweries and contract bottling plants in australia and new zealand breweries in australia include castlemaine perkins brisbane qld  xxxx west end  southwark adelaide sa  west end southwark knappstein enterprise brewery clare sa  knappstein boags launceston tas  james boags little creatures fremantle wa  little creatures white rabbit malt shovel camperdown nsw  james squire new norcia abbey ale hahn camperdown nsw  hahn tooheys lidcombe nsw  tooheys breweries in new zealand include south island speights dunedin  speights north island the pride south auckland  lion castlemaine perkins breweryedit main article castlemaine perkins located in brisbane castlemaines signature beer xxxx bitter was introduced in  the xxxx had been used for a sparkling ale since  south australian brewing companyedit main article south australian brewing company the south australian brewing company was founded in  there were two breweries one in the west end of the adelaide city centre producing west end beers and the other at thebarton on the banks of the river torrens northwest of the city centre producing southwark beers  pronounced suthik the west end brewery was closed between the wars and the operations consolidated with the southwark brewery operations at the thebarton site according to legend the black and red colours of the sa brewing company came about after the west adelaide football club whose colours are black and red defeated port adelaide in the  south australian national football league sanfl australian rules football grand final the legend states that had west adelaide not won the match the brewerys colours would have become the black and white of port adelaidecitation needed west end draught remains the largest selling beer in south australia west end draught is a currently a  abv pale lager first brewed in  the brand is actively involved with the sanfl was the original sponsor of the showdown in the australian football league and is one of the sponsors of the slowdown charity football match the tradition of painting the thebarton brewery chimney with the team colours of the sanfl premiership finalists began in  other beers brewed under the west end brand are west end export west end gold and west end light prior to the acquisition of the brewing assets by lion nathan in  sa brewing split its brewing assets into sa brewing holdings and its diversified operations were formed into a new listed company named southcorp one of southcorps major assets was southcorp wines acquired from the adelaide steamship company in  and subsequently acquired by lion main australian rival the fosters group australian beer brandsedit j boag  sonedit james boags premium james boags premium light boags draught  classic blonde xxx ale james boags pure beers no longer in production boags  boags strongarm boags st george castlemaine xxxxedit xxxx gold xxxx bitter xxxx summer bright lager emu breweryedit emu bitter emu export emu draft hahnedit hahn super dry hahn premium light hahn premium james squireedit james squire logo james squire is produced by the malt shovel brewery in sydney and now that its volume is larger that what can be produced at that brewery some of the james squires beers are produced at various locations around australia under the guidance of the head brewer at the malt shovel brewery the beer is named after the convict brewer james squire who grew australias first hops and created australias first commercial brewery the brewery has won various awards including champion australasian brewery  and  australian international beer awards and best bohemianstyle pilsener  world beer cup regular brewsedit as of september update the malt shovel brewery manages a range of brews under the james squire brand one fifty lashes pale ale the swindler summer ale the chancer golden ale nine tales amber ale four wives pilsener stowaway india pale ale jack of spades porter the constable copper ale hop thief  americanstyle pale ale cidersedit orchard crush apple and pear ciders speciality brewsedit occasionally 